                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Pearson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay instructs Mr. Pearson to demand an indemnity of $50,000, and to obtain
                    sufficient assurance that engagements will be carried out. The President will
                    not brook delay, and prompt settlement must be insisted upon.)</p>
            </div>
